"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-11-usa-win-2024-olympics-kenya-lead-other-african-countries-on-medal-table\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published  on  By  The USA won the XXXIII edition of the Olympic Games on Sunday in Paris, but it was just by the skin of their teeth.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 35, \"end\": 41, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Super_Bowl_XXXIII\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"XXXIII\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Super_Bowl_XXXIII\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Super_Bowl_XXXIII\"}, {\"begin\": 84, \"end\": 89, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999717033465, \"rank\": 2.829657368433765e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They topped the 2024 Olympics medal table by winning 40 gold medals after the final of the last event of the games was decided on Sunday.\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They only finished above China by winning more silver medals than the Asian giants, scooping 44 while their foes had 27.\", \"from\": 275, \"to\": 395, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 300, \"end\": 305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6170592574389325, \"rank\": 0.6201272451289106, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 345, \"end\": 350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"score\": 0.9951762200145055, \"rank\": 0.004847135154074037, \"text\": \"Asian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China also won 40 golds but managed only 27 silvers.\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 397, \"end\": 402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6170592574389325, \"rank\": 0.6201272451289106, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China were the last team, apart from the US, to top the standings when they did it on home soil at the 2008 Beijing Games.\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 451, \"end\": 456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6170592574389325, \"rank\": 0.6201272451289106, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 492, \"end\": 494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9995990473737765, \"rank\": 0.0004010858596488283, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US women's basketball team helped to seal their country's dominance by edging hosts France to win the final gold medal of the Games.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 711, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 579, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9995990473737765, \"rank\": 0.0004010858596488283, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999958961552773, \"rank\": 3.899334760227371e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans also won the most total medals, with 126 to China's 91, after winning 42 bronze medals as against China's 24.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 713, \"end\": 726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 0.9999999999704414, \"rank\": 2.925361039289575e-11, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Japan were third with 20 gold, 12 silver and 13 bronze for a total of 45, while Australia were in fourth place with 18 gold, 19 silver and 16 bronze for a total of 53.\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 1005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 838, \"end\": 843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999497079620941, \"rank\": 4.9019811488720295e-05, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9397164506533369, \"rank\": 0.05613431634604896, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hosts France were in fifth place with 16 gold, 26 silver and 22 bronze for a total of 64.\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1096, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999958961552773, \"rank\": 3.899334760227371e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, only 12 African teams made it to the medal table.\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenya led the lot after garnering four gold, two silver and five bronze for a total of 11 to finish in 17th place.\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1272, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9788092275026996, \"rank\": 0.021648775100130035, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other African countries that made the medal table include Algeria, joint 39th with two gold and one bronze for a total of three.\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1332, \"end\": 1339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999997950503922, \"rank\": 2.0493611529252976e-07, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The others are South Africa in joint 44th with a total of six medals (1 gold, 3 silver, 2 bronze), and Ethiopia in 47th with a total of four (1 gold, 3 silver).\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1419, \"end\": 1431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999972022028972, \"rank\": 2.796482398412708e-06, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1507, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999977042106344, \"rank\": 2.2957945358060356e-06, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Egypt and Tunisia were joint 52nd with a total of three medals each, comprising one gold, one silver and one bronze medal.\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1566, \"end\": 1571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5675060820015063e-14, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1576, \"end\": 1583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998781378044479, \"rank\": 0.00012183049789528062, \"text\": \"Tunisia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"B